OL,3,CSiblings separated during the war have
OL,4,Cbeen reunited after 80 years
OL,6,FMay said "I always thought of them and
OL,7,Fthey say that they always thought of
OL,8,Fme and they wanted to look for me, it
OL,9,Fis just one of those things. When I
OL,10,Fmet them when I met Ronnie and June it
OL,11,Ffelt as though we had never been
OL,12,Fapart, it didn't seem strange it just
OL,13,Fseemed normal"
OL,15,FMay remembers getting the train to
OL,16,FManchester and phoning all the
OL,17,FHampsons in the phonebook. June said
OL,18,Fshe went into the Salvation Army to
OL,19,Fask about the details of the adoption
OL,20,Fbut they couldn't give her any details.
